/README.md) | [English](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch-protocol-http/README.en.md) | [CHANGELOG](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/fetch-protocol-http/CHANGELOG.md)\n\n`@byted-service/fetch` `http` / `https` protocol extention.\n\n1. Support [public network traffic audit](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnkzpXYEgjWpI797a7EMXH2c#).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/fetch-protocol-http --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n> Currently it is built-in in @byted-service/fetch, actually can be used without any operation.\n\n```ts\nimport { fetch } from '@byted-service/fetch';\nimport { handle } from '@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http';\n\nfetch.register('http', handle);\nfetch.register('https', handle);\n\n(async () => {\n    const resp = await fetch('http://www.domain.com/xxx');\n\n    console.log(await resp.text());\n})();\n```\n\n## API\n\n### fetch(url[, options])\n\nThe parameters of `@byted-service/fetch` have been extended. Generally, It is set by framework, and user unaware.\n\n<details>\n  <summary>History</summary>\n\n-   `v1.3.0`: Support `options.enableHttpMesh`. Support `http://` protocol to work with `Mesh`.\n\n</details>\n\n-   `url`: request url.\n-   `options`:\n    -   `enableHttpMesh`: Whether to send request through `http egress mesh`, the default value is `false`. Different from `enableMesh`, this parameter is only applicable to `http://` protocol, if you need `http://` protocol to work with `mesh`, you can enable this.\n\n## HTTP Egress Mesh\n\nFor historical reasons:\n\n1. `options.enableMesh` existed before `Mesh` supported the `http://` protocol and defaulted to `true`.\n2. `Mesh`'s `http://` protocol does not support `ip:port` and does not work for all `http://` protocol use cases.\n\nTherefore, it is impossible to pass all `http://` protocol traffic to `Mesh` by default, and it is impossible to change the default value of `options.enableMesh` to `false`, so it can only to add the `options.enableHttpMesh` to decide whether should `http://` protocol work with `Mesh`.\n\n**For people who is determined to allow the `http://` protocol to work with `Mesh`, you can set `options.enableHttpMesh = true`.**\n"},"1.0.3":{"_npmVersion":"lerna/undefined/node@v14.18.1+x64 (linux)","maintainers":[{"name":"nodejs-team","email":"nodejs-team@bytedance.com"}],"devDependencies":{"http-proxy-agent":"^4.0.1"},"files":["lib","index.js"],"gitHead":"ce78ed18ba735fbbe19f13d3b1ce932bbe232596","main":"index.js","readmeFilename":"README.en.md","_nodeVersion":"14.18.1","_npmUser":{"email":"nodejs-team@bytedance.com","name":"nodejs-team"},"author":"","repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service"},"dist":{"integrity":"sha512-4y6TSjs2ma1zr1jKTvOhcdxmAl9jLuYH3zrueH3ikZWDlxAEuUqLlF77h+3/jCNCeDMziHUW38JcB9xp2sqIYw==","shasum":"2c25b1800590b0642ddc28d72f0ce5bb9efb526f","tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http/-/fetch-protocol-http-1.0.3.tgz"},"license":"MIT","scripts":{"build":"rm -rf lib && ../../node_modules/.bin/tsc","prepublish":"npm run build","test":"ROUTE_IP=10.227.30.24 RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=boe ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node"},"version":"1.0.3","_id":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http@1.0.3","dependencies":{"@byted-service/fetch-core":"^2.2.2","@byted/node-fetch":"^2.6.3","tslib":"^1.9.3"},"description":"http and https protocol for @byted-service/fetch","name":"@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http","readme":"# @byted-service/fetch-protocol-http\n\n[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/fetch-protocol-http)\n\n[简体中文](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/b